main event: Visual and radar sightings of three unidentified objects over San Juan, Puerto Rico on July 8, 1962.
interesting points: The radar targets were determined to be manmade,There was a failure to identify whether the objects were meteorological balloons or secret aircraft,The visual observation was noted as indistinct, which made it insufficient for definite identification, The report mentions that the objects were moving in a level course, An orange colored light was observed, described as oval and slightly larger than a star.
sighted object: three unidentified objects detected by radar and visually observed
